{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_brookland_ver01/data/sn84026749/00205696386/1930100301/0593.xml":{"full_text":"LOVE WHISPER\nHOLDS OP TRIAL\nCHICAGO, Oct. 3.\u2014Attorney\nSol Tannenbaum whispered in\nJudge Joseph Burke\u2019s ear and won\na continuance in the case of Ben\njamin Markowitz, 17, high school\nstudent, who has confessed at\ntempts to extort money from resi\ndents of Hyde Park by writing\nj them death threats.\nAnd this is what Attorney Tan\nnenbaum whispered:\n\u201cJudge, I am going to be mar\nlied to the defenant\u2019s sister.\u201d\nJudge Burke beaihed.\n\"Case continued till Wednes-\ni day.\u201d\nAssistant State\u2019s Attorney Evert\nO. Hutchins had objected, on the\ngrounds that he feared attempts\nto influence witnesses. Judge\nBurke said he would see no such\nefforts were made.\nMarkowitz has confessed trying\nto extort a total of $7,500 from\nMrs. Henry Stein, 4635 Greenwood\nAve., and Julius H. Manheimer,\nt 4459 Drexel Ave.\n\nCommodity Prices\nApt to Go Lower\nCHICAGO, Oct. 3 (I.NJS.).\nLower commodity prices and the\nreturn of prosperity were fore\nj. cast by R. W. Lyons, executive\nvice president of the National\nChain Store Association, which\nopened a three-day convention\nhere. He said:\n\"The present economic situ\nation was brought about by the\nattempt of many organizations\nt' maintain fictitiously high\nprice, levels.\u201d\nDelegates to the convention\nrepresent more than 60,000 re\ntail stores, with annual sales of\n$9,000,000.\nHyw\nFrom the Prince in his I\ngilded palace to the beggar in\nthe street each proclaims\nhis status by his clothes...in I\nthe world, or in the world of M\nmake-believe.\nAll crafts, trades and\nprofessions are represented\nin Home Laundry patron- M\nage. Everything is laun-\ndered thoroughly, delivered\npromptly, and the charge B\nis moderate. Are we serv- B\nIng you this week?\n\nSET OF TEETH\nthe jSI\u00ab\nfjw pr,ces ;\u00abo\nDR. LEON Cor. 1th B a W.\ni i\nNEWS\n/n Todays\nCLASSIFIED ADS\nLOST\u201