 boy arose at his usual i\ntime and was asked by his 1\nwidowed mother if he wanted 1\nbreakfast, which he refused.\nHe is said to have threatened 1\nto kill himself sometime before.\nHe went to the woodhouse some i\ntime during the day, built up a\nstack of block wood, placed the\nrope around his neck, and kicked\nthe wood from beneath him.\nSpecial I\nSmS? I\nSaturday B\n3-Piece Bed Outfit I\nin\nMetal Bed, <T 7 C\nCoil Spring I\nand Mattress F r\nA remarkable value offered to show\nhow very inexpensive it is to buy here.\nThis outfit includes a wood-finished\nmetal bed, coil spring and a high-grade\nmattress. Specially priced without sac\nrificing quality.\nPET|R GROGAN a SONS CQ\nOpen a JL\nCharge \\J' Weekly\nAKmn 819 N.W,\nGROSNER'S\n1325:F:STREET\nChoose\nA special that comes\nJ at the very start of\nTopcoat weather. No\nT restrictions\u2014Your ab-\nsolute choice of any\nVJ topcoat in the house\nat these two low prices\nCoat\nIn the House!\nOur Entire Stock of\nKuppenheimer\nGrosner\nTopcoats Included\nGroup One Group Two\n4\nFeature \u2018s\u2014Fall Hats,ss\n\u00a9IDOOEIDJ\n132 S F STREET\nTHE WASHINGTON TIMES\nauthority to delay tn 'reporting until\nNovember 1. 1\u00bb3O:\nJohn C. Aiderman. dot U. 8. 8.\nColorado; Carl R. Armsbruat dot. U.\n8. R Went Virginia; Jamoa M. Farrln.\nJr.. from (J 3. 3. Memphla; Oerald L.\nHuff, from U. 8. 8. Colorado. Henry J.\nMc\u00dfoberta det. U. 8. 8. Nevada: John\np Rembert Jr., det. U. 8. 8. Went\nVirginia; Stanley C. Strong, det. U. 8.\n8. Momphla; Deloe L. Welt. det. TJ.\n8. 3 Nevada; Calvin A. Walker. Ir..\ndet U. 8. 8. Colorado.\nMEDICAL CORPS\nLieut Comdr. Irving W. Jacoba (MC)\nto U. 8. Naval Hoapltal, Washington.\nD. C.\nLieut. Comdr. Julius F. Neuborger\n(MC) to Naval Air Station. Lakehurst\nN. J.\nLieut. Harvey W. Miller (MC) to\nU. S. Naval Hospital, Mare Island.\nCalif.\nMisfitting Clothes\nHolds Jail Fugitive\nMEMPHIS, Tenn., Oct. 3.\u2014Ar\nrested because misfitting clothes\naroused a detective\u2019s suspicion,\nLeo Parquette, 30, of Detroit,\nMich., told police that he es\ncaped two weeks ago from prison\nat Jackson, Miss., where he said\nhe was serving a 30-year sentence\nfor murder.\nUnder questioning at police\nheadquarters, Parquette began\nthe telling of a tale which in\ncluded assertions that he killed\nJohn LaFrance 11 years ago at\nAnchorville, Mich., in an argu\nment over the collection of a\nsl4 debt.\nCHINESE ACTOR\nTO GOME BACK\nTOKYO, Oct. 3\u2014Mei Lan-\nFang, famous Chinese female im\npersonator, who has just finished\na tour of six months in the United\nStates, says he believe his pres\nentation of Chinese drama cre\nated much good-will between\nAmerica and China.\nMei was in Japan recently on\nhis way back to Peiping, with <he\ntroupe of 22 Chinese, all men.\nwho accompanied him to America.\nHe said the opera in New York\nappealed to him greatly because\nit has characteristics more sim\nilar to those of Chinese drama\nthan do the typical plays of the\nWest.\nMei hopes to go to London next\nyear and then return to America.\nWORSTEDS Aa\n80 SsS\nwith two trousers Lw9\\\nWe're tired of hearing about \"present\nconditions\"! Let's waste no time repeating the I jl\nthreadbare story of \"why things have come\ndown\". The important fact is that rich textured\nworsteds like these haven't sold at S3O for at\nleast ten years. For a long, long time jflN\ntheir double-woven sturdiness and graceful\nmanner have enjoyed well-earned popularity\nin But now, they're back to mlill\nearth \u2014where we can all have the pleasure IftUmiW';\nof wearing them. They've lost none of their [MIW 7\nlustre but a whole lot of their inflated 11n\n\"figures\". They have the distinguished\nappearance of former famous \"fifties\"! They'll Mjlbm n Him\nwear like \"sixty\". And they recognize no Wffl\nsuperiors in style, regardless of price. Yes U\nindeed, times have changed! These new\nS3O Bond Worsteds, with two trousers, are\nhere to tell you so.\nWON\u00a9\nB ||||||||M\n1335 F. 